This paper deals with graphical calculi for representing quantum systems, which falls under the category of quantum computing (cs.QL). The paper also discusses logical underpinnings for automation, which could be categorized under logic in computer science (cs.LO). The encoding of rational arithmetic involves algebraic manipulation, which could be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with generalized symmetries of quantum operations, which could be categorized under scientific computing (cs.SC).
